README:
Building Infinit backend on OS X

--------------------
0. Deployment Target
--------------------
Setting the MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET environment variable ensures that the built
binaries will run on older versions of OS X (at least using the system compiler).

--------------------
1. Install homebrew
--------------------
http://brew.sh

-----------------
2. Install Python
-----------------
Python 2.7: brew install python2
Python 3.2: brew install python32

----------------
3. Install Boost
----------------
brew edit boost

Add the following to where the bjam file is made to ensure boost links with
Python 3.2:
file.write "using python : 3.2 : /usr/local/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.2/bin/python3 : /usr/local/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.2/include/python3.2m : /usr/local/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.2/lib ;\n"

MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET=10.7 brew install --build-from-source --verbose --debut --with-c++11 boost

----------------
4. Build Infinit
----------------
./drake.clang //build
